        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 7:43PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 743 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cheraw, moving west at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Cheraw, Chesterfield, Cheraw State Park, Northeastern Technical
College, Cheraw Municipal Airport, Ruby, Patrick, Mount Croghan,
McFarlan, Chesterfield Ruby Middle School, Cheraw Fish Hatchery,
Alligator Fire Station, Bay Springs Fire Station, and Chesterfield
Detention Center.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
